blog.name: weirdandwackypokefusions
blog.title: Well that's strange!
blog.description:
Welcome!  I create, using the all-mighty classic Microsoft XP Paint, my own pokemon fusions. All the sprites come from pokestadium and usually people on deviantart/ the xy/sun&moon sprite project. I don't own any of the sprite used, I just fuse them! 
REQUESTS ARE OPEN! Ask Box: 3/15.
PLEASE FEEL FREE TO DRAW MY FUSIONS!!  I absolutely love it when people draw them! There's no need to ask either! Just make sure you tag me so them I can see it!
I hope you enjoy my fusions!

summary: Mega Sablette Mega Sableye and Mega Banette fusion Ghost/Dark Type Ability: Glue Splatter - When it enters the battlefield, glue...
caption:
Mega Sablette

Mega Sableye and Mega Banette fusion

Ghost/Dark Type

Ability: Glue Splatter - When it enters the battlefield, glue is splattered everywhere.  When the opposing pokemon enters the battlefield, their speed stat is lowered by 2. This entry hazard can be cleared by rain.

Stats: HP - 70, Atk - 150, Def - 130, SpA - 100, SpD - 110, Spe - 50

The Fake Gemstone Pokemon

A doll which has been possessed.  It wishes to be just like Sableye and will glue fake gemstones onto itself to make it look more appealing to others. However, it is not very good at using glue and spills a lot of it everywhere and will put too much glue on the gems it sticks on itself. It carries a glue bottle everywhere with it, just in case it needs to stick something onto its body.  Only its legs show.

Request for @asktheboxghosts.  I hope you like it! So, I honestly don’t know why I did the giant glue bottle. I don’t even know where the inspiration came from.  It just happened.

blog.name: pokegodsandmissingno
blog.title: P̵o̵K̸é̴G̸o̸D̷s̸ and Frightful Things to Come?
blog.description: There is a growing desire and expectation of humans here on Earth in making full contact with PoKéMoN who are still unknown. Back in 1995, when I saw my first UPM (Unindexed Pocket Monster), I found out very quickly that other people thought you were totally crazy if you said you saw such things. The world has changed quite a bit since then when I was a child. In fact, in late 1997, a poll taken in Kanto shows that for the first time ever, more than fifty percent of residents now believe in PokéGODS's. Since then, there have been polls that put the figure at over eighty percent or more.

summary: If you have no soul and the capability to ruin lives for money, sharing isn't an option --------------------------------------...
caption:
If you have no soul and the capability to ruin lives for money, sharing isn’t an option

————————————–

Keahi: Mom? How come those business guys don’t just ask to share? We would share right?
Baloo: Of course we would. If we knew for sure they weren’t out to destroy the land and wouldn’t overstep their boundaries. I’m sure your dad and grandparents would be willing to share
Keahi: Oh… You know they wouldn’t be fair don’t you..?
Baloo: In my experience people who want money and don’t understand the sentimental value of something, tend to shoot themselves in the leg about it later

Keahi: How so?
Baloo: Well… My home, the Valelands was a place of mostly nature. Lysandre Industries attempted to buy out most of the land for fracking and the natural materials. Once the dragons and people of the area figured out what was happening and realized they were deceived… Ehehe
Keahi: They were real upset yeah?
Baloo: Super upset. They ran every non native person out of the area and through generations we became wary of any visitors. They were mostly upset by the damage to area they considered sacred. The land that had been in their family for generations was the same they wanted to be there for generations afterwards. That’s why sharing would be pretty hard bud.  We want this land to be here for you and all who come after you
Keahi: Oooh… Then I’ll help you and da protect it yeah? If its important to the family, its important to me!
